@page "/system-info"
@rendermode InteractiveServer

<PageTitle>System Overview</PageTitle>

<h2>Welcome to the Customer Login Statistics Web Application</h2>
<p class="text-secondary">
    This system provides a complete solution for collecting, managing, analyzing, and visualizing
    login statistics from multiple GOBENCH customers.
    It supports manual and automated XML uploads, interactive dashboards, Excel exports,
    activity overview widgets, and a fully documented REST API.
</p>

<hr />

<h3>Main Features</h3>

<ul class="list-group mb-4">

    <!-- Upload -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>1. Upload Page</strong><br />
        Upload XML login statistics to specific customer folders.<br />
        Features:
        <ul>
            <li>Select customer from dropdown or create a new customer name</li>
            <li>Automatic backup of existing files before uploading new ones</li>
            <li>File validation (XML only)</li>
            <li>Safe storage into structured customer directories</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <!-- Files -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>2. Files Page</strong><br />
        View and manage all uploaded XML files grouped by customer.<br />
        Functions:
        <ul>
            <li>Download raw XML files</li>
            <li>Download Excel-converted files</li>
            <li>Delete XML files</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <!-- Dashboard -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>3. Dashboard</strong><br />
        A fully interactive chart-based dashboard visualizing login statistics.<br />
        Features:
        <ul>
            <li>Time filtering via <b>From</b> and <b>To</b> date selectors</li>
            <li>Switch between <b>Year view</b> and <b>Month view</b></li>
            <li>Chart type selection: <b>Bar chart</b> or <b>Line chart</b></li>
            <li>Export chart as PNG</li>
            <li>Supports multiple customers at once</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <!-- REST API -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>4. REST API for Automated Uploads</strong><br />
        Systems can upload XML data programmatically.<br />
        Features:
        <ul>
            <li>POST endpoint for uploading statistics</li>
            <li>API Key authentication</li>
            <li>Direct integration with server storage</li>
            <li>Full compatibility with the manual Upload workflow</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <!-- Home Dashboard -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>5. Home Overview Dashboard</strong><br />
        A visual summary of system activity.<br />
        Widgets include:
        <ul>
            <li><b>Recent 5 Uploads</b> list</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>Technical Features</h3>

<ul class="list-group mb-4">

    <!-- XML Parsing -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>XML Parsing Engine</strong><br />
        Fully recursive XML parser extracting:
        <ul>
            <li>Year / Half-Year / Quarter / Month / Week / Day levels</li>
            <li>User and UserGroup login counts</li>
            <li>Nested hierarchical statistics</li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <!-- Excel Export -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>Advanced Excel Export</strong><br />
        XML files can be converted into a multi-sheet XLSX file with:
        <ul>
            <li>Formatted Total Statistics sheet</li>
            <li>User hierarchy sheet</li>
            <li>UserGroup hierarchy sheet</li>
            <li>Stats hierarchy sheet</li>
            <li><b>Numeric columns exported as true Number type</b></li>
            <li><b>AutoFilter enabled on every sheet</b></li>
            <li><b>Freeze Panes enabled (first row locked)</b></li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <!-- Chart Rendering -->
    <li class="list-group-item">
        <strong>Chart Rendering Technology</strong><br />
        Dashboard charts powered by Chart.js with:
        <ul>
            <li>Dynamic datasets per customer</li>
            <li>Color auto-assignment</li>
            <li>PNG export with spacing and clean layout</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>How to Use the Application</h3>
<ol class="mb-4">
    <li>Upload XML files via the <strong>Upload</strong> page.</li>
    <li>Manage, download, or delete files in <strong>Files</strong>.</li>
    <li>Visualize login stats using <strong>Dashboard</strong>.</li>
    <li>Automate uploads using the <strong>REST API</strong>.</li>
    <li>Check system activity on the <strong>Home</strong> page.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<p class="text-secondary">
    If you need new features, chart types, Excel formats, API extensions, or performance improvements,
    please contact the system administrator.
</p>
